Hi! New to HubSpot and HubL
I've been trying to create a simple image and text module using dnd with an default 50% image on the left side and 50% image on the right side, but the "slider" for the width isn't showing up and the image isn't 100% with of the dnd_module
I've been looking at this example, but even when copying the entire thing I'm not given the "width-slider" shown in the image below
Below is my current code (sorry for the bad formatting)
```{% dnd_area "body_dnd_area" %}
	{% dnd_section 
    vertical_alignment='MIDDLE'
    %}
	{% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/linked_image', 
          width=6, 
          offset=0, 
          img={
            "src": "<https://via.placeholder.com/150>",
            "alt": "Placeholderimage",
          } %}
	{% end_dnd_module %}
	{% dnd_module path='@HubSpot/rich_text', width=6, offset=6, label="Rich Text" %}
	{% module_attribute "html"%}
	&lt;h3&gt;Rich text&lt;/h3&gt;
	{% end_module_attribute %}
	{% end_dnd_module %}


	{% end_dnd_section %}
	{% end_dnd_area %}```
